\fs54 \cf0 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs50 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups whole milk\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups water\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 teaspoons kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup coarse ground cornmeal\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 tablespoons unsalted butter\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 ounces sharp Cheddar, shredded\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b\fs54 \cf0 DIRECTIONS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa160\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs50 \cf3 Place the milk, water, and salt into a large, heavy-bottomed pot over medium-high heat and bring to a boil. Once the milk mixture comes to a boil, gradually add the cornmeal while continually whisking. Once all of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cornmeal/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 cornmeal}} has been incorporated, decrease the heat to low and cover. Remove lid and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 whisk}} frequently, every 3 to 4 minutes, to prevent {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grits/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 grits}} from sticking or forming lumps; make sure to get into corners of pot when whisking. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is creamy. \uc0\u8232 Remove from the heat, add the pepper and butter, and whisk to combine. Once the butter is melted, gradually whisk in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 cheese}} a little at a time. Serve immediately.\
